.SH "NAME"
jwt \- decode and verify JSON Web Tokens
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBjwt\fP [\fIOPTIONS\fP] [\fITOKEN\fP]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
\fBjwt\fP decodes and optionally verifies JSON Web Tokens (JWTs). It can display
the header, payload, or signature of a JWT token, and verify the signature
using various algorithms.
.sp
By default, the payload is displayed. The token can be provided as an argument
or read from standard input. The token must be in the standard JWT format with
three base64url\-encoded parts separated by dots.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.SS "Output Selection"
.sp
These options are mutually exclusive. Specifying more than one is an error.
.sp
\fB\-H\fP, \fB\-\-header\fP
.RS 4
Display the JWT header (algorithm, type, etc.).
.RE
.sp
\fB\-P\fP, \fB\-\-payload\fP
.RS 4
Display the JWT payload/claims. This is the default.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-S\fP, \fB\-\-signature\fP
.RS 4
Display the raw signature (base64url decoded).
.RE
.sp
\fB\-A\fP, \fB\-\-all\fP
.RS 4
Display all parts as a JSON object with \fBheader\fP, \fBpayload\fP, and
\fBsignature\fP keys.
.RE
.SS "Verification"
.sp
\fB\-v\fP, \fB\-\-verify\fP=\fISECRET_OR_KEY\fP
.RS 4
Verify the JWT signature. The value can be:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
A literal string secret for HMAC algorithms (HS256, HS384, HS512)
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\f(CR@file\fP to read the key from a file (for RSA/ECDSA public keys)
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\f(CR@\-\fP or \f(CR\-\fP to read the secret or key from standard input (token must be provided as argument)
.RE
.RE
.SS "General"
.sp
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP
.RS 4
Show help message and exit.
.RE
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.sp
\fITOKEN\fP
.RS 4
The JWT token to decode or verify. Must be in standard JWT format:
header.payload.signature. If not provided as an argument, the token is
read from standard input.
.RE
