.sp
.sp
macOS ships with LibreSSL by default. To use PS256 or EdDSA algorithms,
install OpenSSL via Homebrew:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
brew install openssl
export PATH="/opt/homebrew/opt/openssl/bin:$PATH"
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SH "NOTES"
.sp
The tool automatically detects the signature algorithm from the JWT header
and uses the appropriate verification method.
.sp
For HMAC algorithms, the verification secret should be the same secret used
to sign the token. For RSA and ECDSA algorithms, you need the public key
corresponding to the private key used to sign the token.
.sp
JWT tokens often contain sensitive information. Be careful when sharing or
logging tokens, especially in production environments.
.SH "SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS"
.sp
Always verify JWT signatures in production environments. Unverified JWTs
should never be trusted.
.sp
Keep signing secrets and private keys secure. Use environment variables or
secure key management systems rather than hardcoding secrets.
.sp
The JWT payload is only base64url\-encoded, not encrypted. Anyone can decode
and read the payload without the signing key.
